{{Quote|I am remembering something I accessed earlier. The chief designer of the Ma'aood funerary temples directed his draftsmen that all obvious passages should be booby-trapped, and all traps should be made as inviting as possible.|Lobot|<ref name="Shield of Lies">''[[Shield of Lies]]''</ref>}}
The '''Ma'aood''' were beings who built wondrous temples.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|272|Ma'aood}}</ref> The [[Ma'aood chief designer|chief designer]] of these [[Ma'aood funerary temple|funerary temples]] ensured that all obvious passages were filled with traps that appeared inviting to beings that entered the temples. The [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]] [[Lobot/Legends|Lobot]] was familiar with this Ma'aood practice.<ref name="Shield of Lies" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Ma'aood were first mentioned in ''[[Shield of Lies]]'', a [[1996]] novel written by [[Michael P. Kube-McDowell]].<ref name="Shield of Lies" />

